ENTRY            30395   20260325   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        30395001   20260325   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 14         54
TITLE      Resonant neutron capture in 40Ca
AUTHOR     (A.R.De L.Musgrove, B.J.Allen, J.W.Boldeman,
           D.M.H.Chan, R.L.Macklin)
INSTITUTE  (3AULAUA,3AULAML,1USAORL)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,259,365,1976)
           (J,NSE,82,(2),230,1982) No correction factor for
            neutron capture cross-section is requ.
           (J,AUJ,24,671,1971) Previous exp.with AAEC 3MV VDG.
           (R,AAEC/E-200,1969) Detail of exp.with AAEC 3MV VDG.
           (C,75WASH,1,360,1975) EXFOR30288.004  NG,average.
           (C,75KIEV,3,233,1975) STF,D,G-wid av. s0
FACILITY   (LINAC,1USAORL) ORNL Electron Linear Accelerator
           (VDG) AAEC 3 MeV pulsed Van de Graaff at Lucas heights
            with a flight path of 30 cm for gamma-ray spectra
            experiment.
INC-SOURCE (PHOTO)  for ORELA exp.
           (P-LI7)  for AAEC 3MV Van de Graaff.
SAMPLE     (20-CA-40,ENR=0.9973) 40CaCO3 with
            dimensions 5.2*2.61*0.845 cm and thickness
            0.00875 atoms/b.
           Gamma-ray spectra measurement:
           A granular target (20*20 cm) of natural calcium,
            0.0496 atoms/b.
DETECTOR   (SCIN) Two non-hydrogeneous liquid scintillators.
           The efficiency of the detector was proportional to the
           total gamma ray energy release and was independent of
           the nature of spectrum.
           A 0.5 mm 6Li glass detector was used as the neutron
            flux monitor.
           (GELI) Ge(Li) detector.
           (MOXR) Moxon-Rae detector with a natural cadmium sample
            for the relative energy dependence of the neutron flux
MONITOR    (3-LI-6(N,T)2-HE-4,,SIG) for normalization of capture
            data
METHOD     (TOF) Time of flight, path = 40 m(ORELA) and 30 cm(VDG)
PART-DET   (G)
ANALYSIS   -Capture cross-section measurement.-
           (AREA) A locally modified version of the RPI/ORNL Monte
           Carlo code.
           (SHAPE) For some resonances, when the neutron-width was
           larger than 0.3 * gamma(r),where gamma(r) was the FWHM
           of the resolution function,  the neutron-widths were
           extracted from shape analysis.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by Musgrove, 77/05/24.
HISTORY    (19770406C) KO.
           (19770607U) KO.- 'Aprvd' added. Corrected author's name
           (19790207U) KO. -Add 1ref.-
           (19800118U) KO. -Cosmetic correction in BIB.-
           (19821028U) DG.-Insertion of corrigendum in reference,
            conversion from ISO-QUANT to REACTION formalism.-
           (19930202U) HW.-Sequence institute codes altered.-
           (20090115A) BIB section updated
           (20160922U) VS. Reference C,75WASH corrected.
           (20260325A) VT. Revision in 002-006
ENDBIB              54
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           57
SUBENT        30395002   20260325   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  5         21
REACTION  1(20-CA-40(N,0),,EN)
          2(20-CA-40(N,G),,ARE)
          3(20-CA-40(N,G),,WID/STR)
          4(20-CA-40(N,EL),,WID/RED,,G) for p- and d-wave.
COMMENT    The 89 keV resonance is assigned as s-wave. (It is
            listed as p-wave in BNL-325 3rd vol.I(1973)). This
            resonance is possibly a triplet.
          4In this subentry momentum is only taken to
            distinguish p- and d- wave. More details of
            momentum l are in subentry 30395003
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Below 200 keV the absolute normalization
            error of the capture area is to be better than 10%,
            increasing to about 15% at 300 keV.
           No further information for other resonance parameters.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.R.De L.Musgrove+,J,NP/A,259,365,1976)
            Table 1 and 2
HISTORY    (19821101U) DG.-Convert.From ISO-QUANT to REACTION form
           (19830426A) DG.-Reduction of number of data
            fields after BNL 83/03/21 letter.
           (20260324A) VT. Data restored is presented in the
            data source and STATUS updated
ENDBIB              21
